---
import Layout from '../components//Layout.astro';
import FullscreenImage from '../components/FullscreenImage.astro';
import NewsItem from '../components/NewsItem.astro';
import * as Image from '../scripts/ImagePath'
---

<Layout>
  <img src={Image.home_cover} class="w-full" />
  <div class="p-10 m-5">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold pb-5">Welcome</h1>

    <p>MoonRay is DreamWorks&apos; open-source,
    <a href="https://research.dreamworks.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/2019-10-02-DreamWorks-Animation-Lumiere-Award-Moonray-Arras.pdf" class="text-blue-600">multi-award-winning</a>, state-of-the-art production MCRT renderer, which has been used on feature films such as How to Train Your Dragon: 
    The Hidden World, The Bad Guys, Puss In Boots: The Last Wish, the newest release, Kung Fu Panda 4, as well as future titles. MoonRay was developed at DreamWorks and is in 
    continuous active development and includes an extensive library of production-tested, physically based materials, a USD Hydra render delegate, multi-machine and cloud rendering 
    via the Arras distributed computation framework.</p>
    <FullscreenImage 
      src={Image.home_paper}
      alt="MoonRay"
      caption="MoonRay"
      width="w-74"
    />

    <p class="pb-5 italic">MoonRay is developed in-house and is maintained by <a href="https://www.dreamworks.com/" class="text-blue-600">DreamWorks Animation</a> for all of their feature film production. Many thanks go to all of the engineers for building and delivering 
    this state of the art MCRT renderer since the very beginning, and to DreamWorks Animation for continuing a long tradition of contributing back to the wider computer graphics community.
    </p>
    <p class="pt-3 pb-5">We invite you to watch our Sizzle Reel!</p>

<div class="relative aspect-video w-full max-w-3xl mx-auto">
  <iframe
    class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full"
    src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/86DW_M38rcE"
    allowfullscreen>
  </iframe>
</div>



    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold pt-10">News &amp; Releases</h1>
