<NewsItem
  date="12-June-2025"
story={`
    <p>
      MoonRay 2.15.0.1 is now available for 
      <a href="https://github.com/dreamworksanimation/openmoonray/releases/tag/openmoonray-2.15.0.1" class="text-blue-600">download</a>.
    </p>

    <p>This is a major release:</p>

    <ul class="list-disc list-inside pl-4">
      <li>New developer <a href="https://github.com/dreamworksanimation/rats" class="text-blue-600">regression suite</a>. Includes release of ~400 tests and automated canonical image generation</li>
      <li>Added NUMA architecture support. Includes affinity controls for CPU / Memory to achieve better performance on NUMA architecture machines</li>
      <li>New <a href="https://docs.openmoonray.org/user-reference/tools/rdla_gui/" class='text-blue-600'>rdla_gui</a> program that creates a GUI from rdla objects and parameters and updates a delta .rdla file for real time control when rendering with moonray_gui</li>
      <li>New per-BSDF lobe lightsets</li>
      <li>New FOV attribute to the FisheyeCamera</li>
      <li>New <a href="https://docs.openmoonray.org/user-reference/scene-objects/maps/TwoSidedMap/" class="text-blue-600">TwoSidedMap</a></li>
      <li>Various other documentation updates, bug fixes and improvements</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      See the <a href="https://github.com/dreamworksanimation/openmoonray/discussions/187" class="text-blue-600">release notes</a> for a complete list of changes.
    </p>
`}

/>

<NewsItem
  date="20-December-2024"
  story={`MoonRay 1.7.0.0 is now available for <a href="https://github.com/dreamworksanimation/openmoonray/releases/tag/openmoonray-1.7.0.0" class="text-blue-600">download</a>.
    <p>This is a minor release:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside pl-4">
      <li>Improved <a href="https://github.com/dreamworksanimation/openmoonray/blob/main/building/Rocky9/rocky9_build.md" class="text-blue-600">Rocky9</a> and <a href="https://github.com/dreamworksanimation/openmoonray/blob/main/building/macOS/macOS_build.md" class="text-blue-600">MacOS</a> build instructions and CMake presets for hdMoonray in Houdini</li>
      <li>XPU mode now accelerates both regular rays and occlusion rays for NVIDIA GPUs</li>
      <li>New <a href="https://docs.openmoonray.org/user-reference/scene-objects/lights/PortalLight/" class="text-blue-600">PortalLight</a></li>
      <li>New support for <a href="https://docs.openmoonray.org/user-reference/how-to-guides/shadow-ray-manipulation/#min-shadow-distance" class="text-blue-600">min_shadow_distance</a></li>
      <li>Adds Cryptomatte support to hdMoonRay</li>
      <li>New shared memory framebuffer interface for sending framebuffer data between processes</li>
      <li>Various other documentation updates, bug fixes and improvements</li>
    </ul>
    <p>See the <a href="https://github.com/dreamworksanimation/openmoonray/discussions/173" class="text-blue-600">release notes</a> for a complete list of changes.</p>`}
/>

